<%- include('partials/navbar') -%>

<main class="flex flex-col items-center text-center mt-5">
  <section class="about px-10 lg:px-44">
    <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-5">What is Fire Finder?</h1>
    <p class="text-left mb-5">Fire Finder is designed to make wildfire information as simple and easy to find as possible. Here you can find fire data from multiple sources in one place, without anything getting in your way.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="flex flex-col items-center bg-neutral px-10 lg:px-44">
    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold my-5">How it works:</h3>
    <p class="text-left mb-2">Fire Finder automatically updates its data every six hours, to ensure you have access to the most recent information available. Each triangle represents a fire, colored according to containment. They are also sized based on how many acres they've burned.</p>

    <section class="flex flex-wrap mb-5">
